delRouter(): ModelRouter {\n  return getFeatureFlagSync('model_routing_client_side')\n    ? new LocalRouter(new RuleBasedTurnClassifier(), defaultSelector)\n    : new RemoteApiRouter(getFactoryApiFetcher());\n}\n```\n\nSo an experiment that runs the classifier locally needs **only a CLI binary update** — no backend deploy, satisfying your goal #3. Conversely, prod can ship `RemoteApiRouter` to keep the model + heuristics server-side.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Improvement #4 — Offline classifier harness\n\nBecause `TurnClassifier` is a pure interface and the package has no Next.js / AWS deps, we can ship a tiny CLI tool:\n\n```bash\n# apps/scripts/src/router-eval/run.ts\n$ tsx apps/scripts/src/router-eval/run.ts \\\n    --fixtures evals/router/fixtures.jsonl \\\n    --classifier fireworks \\\n    --out evals/router/results.jsonl\n```\n\n`fixtures.jsonl` is one `ClassifierSignals` per line plus an expected label:\n\n```jsonl\n{\"signals\":{\"lastUserMessage\":\"list files\",\"recentToolCalls\":[{\"name\":\"LS\",\"status\":\"success\"}],\"hasImages\":false,\"turnCount\":1,\"surface\":\"interactive-tui\",\"isSubAgentSession\":false,\"sessionId\":\"x\"},\"expected\":\"TRIVIAL\"}\n```\n\nThe runner instantiates the *same* `FireworksTurnClassifier` used in production with a stub `getApiKey` (reads from `FIREWORKS_API_KEY` env), runs it over the file, and writes per-row predictions plus a summary (precision/recall per label, classifier latency p50/p99, fallback rate). For a unit test, we substitute a `FixtureTurnClassifier` that just looks up `signals.sessionId` in a hash map.\n\nSame code path → same behaviour → no drift between prod and offline.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Improvement #5 — All five signals available to the classifier\n\nThe shared `ClassifierSignals` interface (Section 1) carries everything you listed:\n\n| Signal | Source |\n|---|---|\n| current message | `signals.lastUserMessage` (already in PR) |\n| session context | `signals.recentToolCalls`, `signals.conversationSummary