            "plan": "## Refined plan (incorporating your feedback)\n\n- Shared code lives in `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/` with new exports wired in `droid-core/package.json` (`./model-router/*`).\n- New backend endpoint goes through `handleRouteMiddleware` + `RateLimitCategory.LLM_PROXY`, same as the messages route.\n- We **keep the single `ModelRoutingAuto` Statsig flag** as the master switch. When `false`:\n  - Auto mode is hidden in the CLI `ModelSelector` and in the Desktop model selector.\n  - The `/api/llm/router/select-model` endpoint returns a deterministic fallback (Opus 4.6) so it never breaks if an old client queries it.\n  - No routing happens anywhere. No sub-flags, no extra knobs.\n- Experiment selection (which policy / which classifier / client-vs-server) is driven by **dynamic config** (`model_routing_config`) under the same flag, so we flip experiments without a second Statsig toggle.\n- Sub-agent signal = `decompSessionType === DecompSessionType.Worker` (reusing existing state).\n\n---\n\n## Package layout — `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/`\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/model-router/\n├── index.ts                     # re-exports public API\n├── types.ts                     # ClassifierSignals, RoutingDecision, ModelOption, SessionSurface, TurnClassification\n├── enums.ts                     # TurnClassification, SessionSurface (re-exports)\n├── selector.ts                  # ModelSelector (classification → ordered ModelOption[])\n├── selector.test.ts\n├── policy.ts                    # RoutingPolicy + combinators (onceAtTurn, everyTurn, onlyForSurface, and/or, expireAfter)\n├── policy.test.ts\n├── classifiers/\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── rule-based.ts            # pure, no deps — moved from PR's classifier.ts\n│   ├── rule-based.test.ts\n│   ├── fireworks.ts             # moved from PR, deps (fetch, getApiKey) injected\n│   ├── fireworks.test.ts\n│   ├── fixture.ts               # signals → expected label from an in-memory map (for tests + offline)\n│   └── prompt.ts                # buildClassifierPrompt (extracted, testable)\n├── router/\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── types.ts                 # ModelRouter interface, ModelRouterDeps\n│   ├── local.ts                 # LocalRouter — runs classifier + selector in-process\n│   ├── local.test.ts\n│   ├── remote.ts                # RemoteApiRouter — calls /api/llm/router/select-model\n│   └── remote.test.ts\n└── README.md                    # short doc (yes, only this directory needs one for cross-package clarity)\n```\n\nPackage exports added to `packages/droid-core/package.json`:\n\n```json\n\"./model-router\": \"./src/model-router/index.ts\",\n\"./model-router/types\": \"./src/model-router/types.ts\",\n\"./model-router/classifiers\": \"./src/model-router/classifiers/index.ts\",\n\"./model-router/router\": \"./src/model-router/router/index.ts\",\n\"./model-router/policy\": \"./src/model-router/policy.ts\",\n\"./model-router/selector\": \"./src/model-router/selector.ts\"\n```\n\nDependencies: `droid-core` already depends on `@factory/common`, `@factory/utils`, `@factory/logging` — everything we need. No new deps, no new workspace.\n\n---\n\n## Core types\n\n```ts\n// packages/droid-core/src/model-router/types.ts\nimport type { ApiProvider, ModelID, ReasoningEffort } from '@factory/common/llm';\n\nexport enum SessionSurface {\n  InteractiveTui = 'interactive-tui',\n  Exec = 'exec',\n  SubAgent = 'sub-agent',\n  Daemon = 'daemon',\n}\n\nexport enum TurnClassification {\n  TRIVIAL = 'TRIVIAL',\n  STANDARD = 'STANDARD',\n  COMPLEX = 'COMPLEX',\n}\n\nexport interface ClassifierSignals {\n  lastUserMessage: string;\n  recentToolCalls: ReadonlyArray<{ name: string; status: 'success' | 'error' }>;\n  hasImages: boolean;\n  turnCount: number;\n  surface: SessionSurface;\n  isSubAgentSession: boolean;\n  parentSessionId?: string;\n  sessionId: string;\n  conversationSummary?: string;\n  hasFailedToolCalls?: boolean;\n}\n\nexport interface ClassifierResult {\n  classification: TurnClassification;\n  confidence: number;\n  latencyMs: number;\n  source: 'fireworks' | 'rule-based' | 'fixture' | 'remote-api';\n}\n\nexport interface TurnClassifier {\n  classify(signals: ClassifierSignals): Promise<ClassifierResult>;\n}\n\nexport interface ModelOption {\n  modelId: ModelID;\n  apiProvider: ApiProvider;\n  reasoningEffort: ReasoningEffort;\n  rank: number;              // 0 = primary\n  rationale: string;\n}\n\nexport interface RoutingDecision {\n  options: ModelOption[];    // ordered; agent picks options[0] by default\n  classification: TurnClassification;\n  classifierResult: ClassifierResult;\n  decidedAt: string;         // ISO timestamp\n  decidedBy: 'client' | 'server';\n  ttlMs: number;             // how long this decision remains valid\n  sessionId: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ModelSelector {\n  select(result: ClassifierResult, signals: ClassifierSignals): ModelOption[];\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Improvement 1 — Agent-driven explicit API call\n\n### Backend endpoint\n\n`apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/router/select-model/route.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport async function POST(request: NextRequest) {\n  return handleRouteMiddleware(\n    request,\n    async ({ user, organization, sessionId }) => {\n      const body = await parseJsonRequest<{ signals: ClassifierSignals }>(request);\n\n      const flags = await getFeatureFlagInstance();\n      const enabled = await flags.checkFlag(FactoryFeatureFlags.ModelRoutingAuto, organization.id);\n      if (!enabled) {\n        return NextResponse.json(fallbackDecision(sessionId));   // Opus 4.6 primary, single option\n      }\n\n      const classifier = getServerClassifier();                  // FireworksTurnClassifier with injected deps\n      const selector = getServerSelector();\n      const router = new LocalRouter({ classifier, selector });  // \"local\" to the backend process\n      const decision = await router.route({ ...body.signals, sessionId });\n\n      Metrics.addToCounter(Metric.ROUTING_DECISION_COUNT, 1, {\n        classification: decision.classification,\n        model: decision.options[0]!.modelId,\n      });\n\n      return NextResponse.json({ ...decision, decidedBy: 'server' });\n    },\n    { requireSessionId: true, rateLimit: RateLimitCategory.LLM_PROXY },\n  );\n}\n```\n\n### CLI agent integration\n\n`apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` gains:\n\n```ts\nprivate effectiveAutoModel: {\n  modelId: string;\n  apiProvider: ApiProvider;\n  reasoningEffort: ReasoningEffort;\n  expiresAt: number;\n  decidedAt: string;\n  decidedBy: 'client' | 'server';\n} | null = null;\n\npublic getEffectiveAutoModel() { return this.effectiveAutoModel; }\npublic setEffectiveAutoModel(decision: RoutingDecision) {\n  const primary = decision.options[0]!;\n  this.effectiveAutoModel = {\n    modelId: primary.modelId,\n    apiProvider: primary.apiProvider,\n    reasoningEffort: primary.reasoningEffort,\n    expiresAt: Date.now() + decision.ttlMs,\n    decidedAt: decision.decidedAt,\n    decidedBy: decision.decidedBy,\n  };\n  // Persist under sessionSettings.effectiveAutoModel so resume works.\n  this.sessionSettings.effectiveAutoModel = this.effectiveAutoModel;\n  this.saveSessionSettings({ async: true, shouldSyncToCloud: true });\n}\n```\n\n### Streaming core call site\n\n`apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` (inside `sendAnthropicMessage`, before building params):\n\n```ts\nif (model === AUTO_MODEL) {\n  const policy = buildRoutingPolicy();   // per-surface\n  const ctx: RoutingPolicyContext = {\n    surface: deps.getSessionSurface(),\n    isSubAgent: deps.isSubAgentSession(),\n    turnNumber: conversationHistory.filter(m => m.role === 'assistant').length,\n    hasEffectiveModel: sessionService.getEffectiveAutoModel() != null,\n    effectiveModelAge: sessionService.getEffectiveAutoModel()\n      ? Date.now() - new Date(sessionService.getEffectiveAutoModel()!.decidedAt).getTime()\n      : Infinity,\n  };\n\n  if (policy.shouldRoute(ctx)) {\n    const signals = buildClassifierSignals({ conversationHistory, sessionService, deps });\n    const decision = await modelRouter.route(signals);\n    sessionService.setEffectiveAutoModel(decision);\n    callbacks.onResolvedModel?.(decision.options[0]!.modelId);\n  }\n\n  const effective = sessionService.getEffectiveAutoModel();\n  if (!effective) {\n    // First call and policy didn't fire — use hard fallback (Opus 4.6)\n    effective = FALLBACK_AUTO_MODEL;\n  }\n  model = effective.modelId;\n  currentAnthropicProvider = effective.apiProvider;\n  reasoningEffort = effective.reasoningEffort;\n}\n```\n\nThe proxy goes back to being a dumb transport: `messages/route.ts` loses `anthropicModelRouter`, `applyRoutingDecision`, `wasAutoRouted`, and the `x-resolved-model` header logic. About 60 lines deleted.\n\n---\n\n## Improvement 2 — Flexible \"when to route\" policy\n\n```ts\n// packages/droid-core/src/model-router/policy.ts\nexport interface RoutingPolicyContext {\n  surface: SessionSurface;\n  isSubAgent: boolean;\n  turnNumber: number;\n  hasEffectiveModel: boolean;\n  effectiveModelAge: number;\n}\n\nexport interface RoutingPolicy {\n  readonly name: string;\n  shouldRoute(ctx: RoutingPolicyContext): boolean;\n}\n\n// Building blocks\nexport const everyTurn: RoutingPolicy = {\n  name: 'every-turn',\n  shouldRoute: () => true,\n};\nexport const onceAtTurn = (n: number): RoutingPolicy => ({\n  name: `once-at-turn-${n}`,\n  shouldRoute: (c) => c.turnNumber === n,\n});\nexport const onlyOnFirstCall: RoutingPolicy = {\n  name: 'once-per-session',\n  shouldRoute: (c) => !c.hasEffectiveModel,\n};\nexport const onlyForSurface = (s: SessionSurface): RoutingPolicy => ({\n  name: `surface-${s}`,\n  shouldRoute: (c) => c.surface === s,\n});\nexport const onlyForSubAgents: RoutingPolicy = {\n  name: 'sub-agents-only',\n  shouldRoute: (c) => c.isSubAgent,\n};\nexport const expireAfter = (ms: number): RoutingPolicy => ({\n  name: `expire-${ms}ms`,\n  shouldRoute: (c) => c.effectiveModelAge > ms,\n});\n\nexport const and = (...ps: RoutingPolicy[]): RoutingPolicy => ({\n  name: `and(${ps.map((p) => p.name).join(',')})`,\n  shouldRoute: (c) => ps.every((p) => p.shouldRoute(c)),\n});\nexport const or = (...ps: RoutingPolicy[]): RoutingPolicy => ({\n  name: `or(${ps.map((p) => p.name).join(',')})`,\n  shouldRoute: (c) => ps.some((p) => p.shouldRoute(c)),\n});\n```\n\nExperiment registry (CLI-side, one file to edit to launch/stop an experiment):\n\n```ts\n// apps/cli/src/models/routingExperiments.ts\nexport const ROUTING_EXPERIMENTS = {\n  'exec-only':       onlyForSurface(SessionSurface.Exec),\n  'subagent-only':   onlyForSubAgents,\n  'first-turn':      onceAtTurn(0),\n  'second-turn':     onceAtTurn(1),\n  'once-per-session':onlyOnFirstCall,\n  'always':          everyTurn,\n  'first-or-stale':  or(onlyOnFirstCall, expireAfter(60_000)),\n} as const satisfies Record<string, RoutingPolicy>;\n\nexport function buildRoutingPolicy(): RoutingPolicy {\n  const experimentName = getDynamicConfig('model_routing_config').get('experiment', 'once-per-session');\n  return ROUTING_EXPERIMENTS[experimentName] ?? onlyOnFirstCall;\n}\n```\n\nAll surface/sub-agent signals are already present on `SessionService` — `getSessionSurface()` returns `Exec` when `isExecMode()` is true, otherwise `InteractiveTui`; sub-agent detection reuses `currentDecompSessionType === DecompSessionType.Worker`.\n\n---\n\n## Improvement 3 — Client vs server routing, pluggable\n\n```ts\n// packages/droid-core/src/model-router/router/types.ts\nexport interface ModelRouter {\n  readonly name: string;\n  route(signals: ClassifierSignals): Promise<RoutingDecision>;\n}\n\n// local.ts — runs classifier + selector in-process\nexport class LocalRouter implements ModelRouter {\n  readonly name = 'local';\n  constructor(private deps: { classifier: TurnClassifier; selector: ModelSelector; ttlMs?: number }) {}\n  async route(signals: ClassifierSignals): Promise<RoutingDecision> {\n    const result = await this.deps.classifier.classify(signals);\n    const options = this.deps.selector.select(result, signals);\n    return {\n      options,\n      classification: result.classification,\n      classifierResult: result,\n      decidedAt: new Date().toISOString(),\n      decidedBy: 'client',\n      ttlMs: this.deps.ttlMs ?? 60_000,\n      sessionId: signals.sessionId,\n    };\n  }\n}\n\n// remote.ts — calls /api/llm/router/select-model\nexport class RemoteApiRouter implements ModelRouter {\n  readonly name = 'remote-api';\n  constructor(private fetcher: (url: string, init: RequestInit) => Promise<Response>) {}\n  async route(signals: ClassifierSignals): Promise<RoutingDecision> {\n    const res = await this.fetcher('/api/llm/router/select-model', {\n      method: 'POST',\n      headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },\n      body: JSON.stringify({ signals }),\n    });\n    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`Router API failed: ${res.status}`);\n    return (await res.json()) as RoutingDecision;\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCLI wiring:\n\n```ts\n// apps/cli/src/models/modelRouter.ts\nexport function getModelRouter(): ModelRouter {\n  const mode = getDynamicConfig('model_routing_config').get('mode', 'server');\n  if (mode === 'client') {\n    return new LocalRouter({\n      classifier: new RuleBasedTurnClassifier(),\n      selector: defaultClientSelector,\n    });\n  }\n  return new RemoteApiRouter(buildFactoryApiFetcher());\n}\n```\n\nSwitching experiments from server → client is a single dynamic-config flip, no backend deploy.\n\n---\n\n## Improvement 4 — Offline classifier harness\n\nBecause the shared package depends on nothing Next.js/AWS-specific, we ship a tsx-based harness:\n\n```ts\n// apps/scripts/src/router-eval/run.ts\nimport fs from 'node:fs';\nimport { FireworksTurnClassifier, RuleBasedTurnClassifier } from '@factory/droid-core/model-router/classifiers';\nimport type { ClassifierSignals, TurnClassifier, TurnClassification } from '@factory/droid-core/model-router/types';\n\ninterface FixtureRow { signals: ClassifierSignals; expected: TurnClassification; }\n\nconst FIXTURE_FILE = process.argv[process.argv.indexOf('--fixtures') + 1];\nconst CLASSIFIER = process.argv[process.argv.indexOf('--classifier') + 1] ?? 'rule-based';\n\nfunction buildClassifier(name: string): TurnClassifier {\n  if (name === 'fireworks') {\n    return new FireworksTurnClassifier({\n      fetch: globalThis.fetch,\n      getApiKey: async () => process.env.FIREWORKS_API_KEY!,\n      timeoutMs: 50,\n    });\n  }\n  return new RuleBasedTurnClassifier();\n}\n\nasync function main() {\n  const classifier = buildClassifier(CLASSIFIER);\n  const rows: FixtureRow[] = fs.readFileSync(FIXTURE_FILE, 'utf8')\n    .trim()\n    .split('\\n')\n    .map((l) => JSON.parse(l));\n\n  let correct = 0;\n  const perLabel: Record<string, { tp: number; fp: number; fn: number }> = {};\n\n  for (const row of rows) {\n    const result = await classifier.classify(row.signals);\n    const ok = result.classification === row.expected;\n    if (ok) correct++;\n    // update per-label counters\n    ...\n    process.stdout.write(JSON.stringify({ ...row, predicted: result }) + '\\n');\n  }\n\n  console.error(`Accuracy: ${(correct / rows.length * 100).toFixed(1)}%`);\n}\nmain();\n```\n\nFixture format (one JSON per line):\n\n```jsonl\n{\"signals\":{\"lastUserMessage\":\"list files\",\"recentToolCalls\":[{\"name\":\"LS\",\"status\":\"success\"}],\"hasImages\":false,\"turnCount\":1,\"surface\":\"interactive-tui\",\"isSubAgentSession\":false,\"sessionId\":\"fx-001\"},\"expected\":\"TRIVIAL\"}\n{\"signals\":{\"lastUserMessage\":\"refactor the whole auth module\",\"recentToolCalls\":[],\"hasImages\":false,\"turnCount\":1,\"surface\":\"interactive-tui\",\"isSubAgentSession\":false,\"sessionId\":\"fx-002\"},\"expected\":\"COMPLEX\"}\n```\n\nUnit tests use `FixtureTurnClassifier` — an in-memory TurnClassifier backed by a `Map<sessionId, TurnClassification>`.\n\nSame `FireworksTurnClassifier` class runs in prod (server endpoint), in the offline harness, and in tests — no drift possible.\n\n---\n\n## Improvement 5 — Signals available to the classifier\n\nAll five are carried via the `ClassifierSignals` interface and populated at the call site by the CLI. The table of sources:\n\n| Signal field | Source |\n|---|---|\n| `lastUserMessage` | Walk conversation history in streaming core |\n| `recentToolCalls`, `conversationSummary`, `hasFailedToolCalls`, `turnCount` | `SessionService.getRecentToolCalls()`, `getCompactionSummary()` |\n| `isSubAgentSession`, `parentSessionId` | `SessionService.getDecompSessionType() === Worker`, `.getParentSessionId()` |\n| `surface` | `deps.isExecMode() ? Exec : InteractiveTui`; sub-agent path sets `SubAgent` explicitly |\n| `hasImages` | Inspect current message for image content blocks |\n\nThe Fireworks prompt builder (`classifiers/prompt.ts`) is extended to include `surface` and `sub_agent` lines when present, so we can train/evaluate on them. Rule-based fallback adds two short-circuits:\n\n- `isSubAgentSession && editCount === 0 && message.length < 120` → STANDARD (sub-agents handle scoped work; avoid over-escalating to COMPLEX)\n- `surface === Exec && allToolsReadOnly && message.length < 200` → TRIVIAL (one-shot exec lookups)\n\n---\n\n## Feature flag handling (single `ModelRoutingAuto`)\n\nThe single flag controls:\n\n1. **Visibility**: `apps/cli/src/components/ModelSelector.tsx` reads `useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.ModelRoutingAuto)` and only lists the Auto option when true. Desktop app's model selector reads the same flag.\n2. **Endpoint**: `/api/llm/router/select-model` short-circuits to a fallback `RoutingDecision` with Opus 4.6 as the only option when the flag is false for the org. The CLI treats that as \"no routing happened\" and continues using the fallback model.\n3. **Streaming core**: if a user hand-types `--model auto` in a CLI where the flag is off, the router still gets called, gets the fallback, and the CLI uses Opus 4.6. No crash path.\n\nExperiment details (which policy, which classifier, client-vs-server) live in the **existing dynamic-config** `default_model_override` family — we add a new `model_routing_config` dynamic config with zod schema:\n\n```ts\n// packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts\nconst ModelRoutingConfigSchema = z.object({\n  experiment: z.enum(['exec-only', 'subagent-only', 'first-turn', 'second-turn', 'once-per-session', 'always', 'first-or-stale']).default('once-per-session'),\n  mode: z.enum(['server', 'client']).default('server'),\n  ttlMs: z.number().int().positive().default(60_000),\n});\nexport const MODEL_ROUTING_CONFIG = 'model_routing_config' as const;\nexport const DYNAMIC_CONFIG_SCHEMAS = {\n  ...existingSchemas,\n  [MODEL_ROUTING_CONFIG]: ModelRoutingConfigSchema,\n};\n```\n\nExperiments are now: flip the flag on for a cohort, set `model_routing_config.experiment = 'first-turn'`, ship.\n\n---\n\n## File-level changes\n\n**New files (shared):**\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/index.ts`, `types.ts`, `enums.ts`\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/selector.ts` + test\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/policy.ts` + test\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/classifiers/{rule-based,fireworks,fixture,prompt,index}.ts` + tests\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/router/{types,local,remote,index}.ts` + tests\n\n**Deleted (backend):**\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/llm-proxy/router/` — whole folder (logic moved to droid-core)\n\n**Modified (backend):**\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/a/v1/messages/route.ts` — remove `anthropicModelRouter.route(...)`, `applyRoutingDecision`, `wasAutoRouted` block, `x-resolved-model` header setting (~60 lines).\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/router/select-model/route.ts` — **new** endpoint.\n\n**New / modified (CLI):**\n- `apps/cli/src/models/modelRouter.ts` — `getModelRouter()` factory (local/remote)\n- `apps/cli/src/models/routingExperiments.ts` — policy registry + `buildRoutingPolicy()`\n- `apps/cli/src/models/buildClassifierSignals.ts` — builds `ClassifierSignals` from conversation + session state\n- `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` — `effectiveAutoModel` slot, getter/setter, persist under `sessionSettings.effectiveAutoModel`\n- `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` — call policy + router before LLM call; drop `x-resolved-model` header read (the onResolvedModel callback stays and is now fired from the agent side)\n- `apps/cli/src/hooks/types.ts`, `streaming/types.ts` — drop `resolvedModel` field on streaming result (agent sets it via callback instead)\n- `apps/cli/src/components/ModelSelector.tsx` — already reads `ModelRoutingAuto` flag; no change needed beyond merge clean-up\n\n**Common package:**\n- `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` — add `model_routing_config` dynamic config with zod schema; keep `ModelRoutingAuto` as single flag.\n- `packages/common/src/session/settings.ts` — add optional `effectiveAutoModel` field to `SessionSettings`.\n\n**droid-core package exports:**\n- `packages/droid-core/package.json` — add `./model-router*` exports.\n\n**Offline harness:**\n- `apps/scripts/src/router-eval/run.ts` — classifier runner\n- `evals/router/fixtures.jsonl` — seed fixtures (start with ~20 hand-labelled)\n- `apps/scripts/package.json` — add `router-eval` script\n\n**Tests to keep + adapt:**\n- All 15 classifier tests → moved to `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/classifiers/*.test.ts`\n- All 24 router tests → split across `selector.test.ts`, `policy.test.ts`, `router/local.test.ts`, `router/remote.test.ts`\n- 8 type tests → become import smoke tests in `model-router/types.test.ts`\n- CLI auto-model tests stay, updated to expect the agent-driven flow instead of `x-resolved-model` header plumbing\n- Backend `anthropic.test.ts` → **deleted**; replaced by new `select-model/route.test.ts`\n- E2E tests (exec + stream-jsonrpc auto-routing) → kept, verified against new flow\n\n---\n\n## Rollout order\n\n1. Land the `droid-core/model-router` package (types, classifiers, policy, selector, router implementations, tests, offline harness). Zero wiring to proxy or CLI yet.\n2. Land the new `/api/llm/router/select-model` endpoint. Messages route untouched.\n3. Switch the CLI's auto-model path from \"send auto, read x-resolved-model header\" to \"call router, set effective model, send concrete model\". Remove old proxy router on the same PR.\n4. Populate `evals/router/fixtures.jsonl` from real sessions and run offline harness to dial in rule-based heuristics before enabling server-side in staging.\n\nLet me know when you're ready for me to start on step 1.",
