          "input": {
            "content": "## Description\n\nReplaces the previous proxy-embedded, per-call auto router with an **agent-driven, policy-based** architecture. The CLI decides _when_ to route via a composable policy, calls an explicit router that returns an ordered list of model options, caches the decision on the session, and sends a concrete model to the proxy. Routing experiments are hot-swappable via a Statsig dynamic config; the classifier is exercised offline via a new eval harness.\n\n### Why the rewrite\n\nThe v1 implementation had a handful of structural issues:\n\n- Classification ran on **every turn** inside the proxy — no way to amortize decisions or bound classifier cost.\n- The agent had **no control** over whether/when to route (classifier was baked into the request path).\n- The classifier received only a thin signal set — no surface (exec/interactive/sub-agent), no conversation shape, no error-recovery state.\n- Only offline-testable by standing up the whole backend.\n- The \"effective model\" was ephemeral (lived only in a response header), so sub-agent spawns and session resumes lost it.\n\n### New architecture\n\n```\n                   ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐\n                   │ @factory/droid-core/model-router       │\n                   │                                        │\n                   │   TurnClassifier                       │\n                   │     ├── FireworksTurnClassifier        │\n                   │     ├── RuleBasedTurnClassifier        │\n                   │     └── FixtureTurnClassifier          │\n                   │                                        │\n                   │   ModelSelector (classification→list)  │\n                   │                                        │\n                   │   RoutingPolicy (composable primitives)│\n                   │     once, everyTurn, onlyForSurface,   │\n                   │     onlyForSubAgents, expireAfter, +   │\n                   │     and/or/not combinators             │\n                   │                                        │\n                   │   ModelRouter                          │\n                   │     ├── LocalRouter (classifier+select)│\n                   │     └── RemoteApiRouter (HTTP → API)   │\n                   └────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                         ▲                         ▲\n                         │                         │\n                         │                         │\n             ┌───────────┴──────────┐   ┌──────────┴──────────┐\n             │ apps/cli             │   │ apps/backend        │\n             │   resolveAutoModel   │   │ /api/llm/router/    │\n             │   Override() per     │   │   select-model      │\n             │   turn               │   │  (LocalRouter+      │\n             │                      │   │   Fireworks)        │\n             └──────────────────────┘   └─────────────────────┘\n                         ▲\n                         │\n             ┌───────────┴──────────┐\n             │ apps/scripts         │\n             │   router-eval        │\n             │   (offline harness)  │\n             │   evals/router/*.jsonl\n             └──────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key pieces\n\n**`@factory/droid-core/src/model-router/`** (new shared package module)\n- `TurnClassifier` interface + three implementations:\n  - `FireworksTurnClassifier` — Fireworks-hosted small model, injected `getApiKey` and `fetch` for prod/test/offline reuse.\n  - `RuleBasedTurnClassifier` — zero-dep heuristic (short read-only → trivial, many edits / errors / refactor keywords → complex).\n  - `FixtureTurnClassifier` — deterministic lookup for unit tests.\n- `ClassifierSignals` now includes `surface` (exec / interactive_tui / sub_agent / daemon), `isSubAgentSession`, `turnCount`, `hasImages`, `hasFailedToolCalls`, `conversationSummary`.\n- `RoutingPolicy` as composable primitives: `onceAtTurn(n)`, `everyTurn()`, `onlyOnFirstCall()`, `onlyForSurface(s)`, `onlyForSubAgents()`, `expireAfter(ms)` + `and`/`or`/`not` combinators.\n- `DefaultModelSelector` maps `TurnClassification` → ordered `ModelOption[]`. Images always force Opus 4.6 primary (MiniMax can't handle them).\n- `LocalRouter` runs classifier+selector in-process; `RemoteApiRouter` POSTs signals to the backend with graceful fallback.\n- **54 new unit tests**, all green.\n\n**`@factory/common`**\n- New `MODEL_ROUTING_CONFIG` Statsig dynamic config (`experiment`, `mode: 'client' | 'server'`, `ttlMs`) — lets us A/B routing experiments without shipping CLI.\n- `EffectiveAutoModel` field added to `SessionSettings` (modelId, apiProvider, reasoningEffort, decidedAt, decidedBy, ttlMs). Cached decision survives session resumes and sub-agent spawns.\n- `ModelRoutingAuto` Statsig gate remains the master switch.\n\n**`apps/backend`**\n- New endpoint `POST /api/llm/router/select-model` wrapped in `handleRouteMiddleware` + `RateLimitCategory.LLM_PROXY`. Instantiates `LocalRouter` with `FireworksTurnClassifier` and returns a `RoutingDecision` JSON payload (ordered model options).\n- **Deleted** the entire `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/llm-proxy/router/` directory (~1800 lines: anthropic.ts, classifier.ts, types, tests).\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/a/v1/messages/route.ts` — stripped auto-routing branch, `x-api-provider: auto` request handling, and `x-resolved-model`/`x-resolved-provider` response headers (~80 lines).\n\n**`apps/cli`**\n- `src/models/modelRouter.ts` — `buildModelRouter()` factory. Server mode (default) → `RemoteApiRouter`. Client mode → `LocalRouter` with `FireworksTurnClassifier` (requires `FACTORY_FIREWORKS_API_KEY`). Mode selection driven by the dynamic config.\n- `src/models/routingExperiments.ts` — registry of 7 named policies (`always`, `once-per-session`, `first-turn`, `second-turn`, `exec-only`, `subagent-only`, `first-or-stale`) keyed by a `RoutingExperimentName` enum.\n- `FeatureFlagService` fetches + caches `modelRoutingConfig` alongside existing flags.\n- `SessionService` gains `getEffectiveAutoModel` / `setEffectiveAutoModel` / `clearEffectiveAutoModel` / `isSubAgentSession` (`decompSessionType === Worker`). Switching away from auto auto-invalidates the cached decision.\n- `createLLMStreamingCore` gains `buildClassifierSignalsFromHistory()` and `resolveAutoModelOverride()`:\n  - Consults the policy to decide if the classifier should run this turn.\n  - Reuses a fresh cached decision if the policy says don't re-route.\n  - Calls `router.route(signals)` if the policy fires, persists the decision, and returns the concrete model override.\n  - The rest of the send path treats auto like any other model — the `x-resolved-model` header read is gone.\n- `useLLMStreaming` + `AgentLoop` wire the `modelRouter` dependency bundle into the core.\n\n**`apps/scripts` + `evals/router/`** (offline eval harness)\n- `npm run router-eval -- --fixtures evals/router/fixtures.jsonl --classifier rule-based` (or `--classifier fireworks` with `--fireworks-api-key`).\n- 20 hand-labeled JSONL fixtures covering trivial/standard/complex across interactive TUI, exec, and sub-agent surfaces, plus edge cases (many edits, error recovery, images, short greetings, search-only sub-agents).\n- Rule-based classifier **100% accuracy** on the seed set. Harness exits non-zero if accuracy < 100%, ready for CI.\n- Same `@factory/droid-core/model-router` code powers the offline harness and production — any improvement shows up in both.\n\n## Related Issue\n\nCloses FAC-17306\n\n## Potential Risk & Impact\n\n- **Feature-flagged**: `ModelRoutingAuto` Statsig gate still gates the entire flow; no impact when off.\n- **Cheaper**: Routing now runs at most once per session by default (`once-per-session` experiment); previously ran every turn.\n- **Agent-controlled**: The agent can opt out of routing per-turn via policy without touching the proxy. Easy to add new experiments (exec-only, first-turn-only, etc.) via dynamic config alone.\n- **Offline-testable**: Classifier improvements are measurable without deploying — PR reviewers can run `npm run router-eval` locally.\n- **Cached decisions**: Persist on the session, so sub-agents spawned by Task inherit the parent's model and session resumes don't re-pay the classifier cost.\n\n## How Has This Been Tested?\n\n- **54 new unit tests** in `@factory/droid-core/src/model-router/` — all classifier, policy, selector, and router modules.\n- **droid-core**: 979 tests pass.\n- **common**: 96 tests pass.\n- **Scripts eval harness**: 100% accuracy on 20 fixtures (`npm run router-eval --workspace=@factory/scripts`).\n- **Backend**: typecheck clean; new endpoint + deletion of legacy router tested locally.\n- **CLI**: `SessionService.auto-model.test.ts` (4 tests) and `createLLMStreamingCore.auto-model.test.ts` pass; remaining suite-level failures in `sessionCwd`, `AgentLoop`, `builtInDroids`, `systemInfo` are pre-existing on `dev` and unrelated.\n- **Lint clean** on all touched files.\n\n## Migration notes for reviewers\n\n- The old `x-resolved-model` header is gone — any telemetry dashboards reading it need to be updated to read from session events (the decision is logged with source/latency).\n- Feature flag behavior is unchanged from the user's perspective: `ModelRoutingAuto` off → no routing, `auto` model selection still works.\n- The rule-based classifier is cheap enough to be the default for sub-agents and exec invocations where we don't want the Fireworks call on the critical path.\n",
