            "new_str": "## ROUTER-1: Update Kimi K2.6 model card with three-pattern structure\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Priority | P1 — High |\n| Status | Ready |\n| Estimate | Small (1-2 hours) |\n| Owner | Leo |\n| Labels | quality, classifier-prompt |\n\n**Description:**\n\nThe production Kimi card in `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/model-cards.ts` uses the old flat weakness list inherited from K2.5 (COBOL/mainframe, Java 7 binary formats, x86-64 assembly, Fortran, C89, etc.) with a `TODO(factory-router): refresh for Kimi K2.6 (inherited from K2.5)` marker.\n\nDuring our April iteration, we restructured the Kimi card around three general failure *patterns* instead of domain lists:\n1. **DECEPTIVELY SIMPLE PROMPTS** — \"Do not equate prompt brevity with task simplicity.\"\n2. **MULTI-STEP WORKFLOWS WITH FEEDBACK LOOPS** — \"Fails when iterating toward a target.\"\n3. **MULTI-SERVICE ORCHESTRATION** — \"Fails on coordinating several interacting services.\"\n\nThis restructuring was validated in offline eval (75 fixtures, 3 trials):\n- Modal accuracy: **75.0% → 82.7%** (+7.7pp)\n- Macro F1: **0.694 → 0.788** (+0.094)\n- Unstable fixtures: **25.0% → 10.7%** (-14.3pp)\n\nThe improved card also includes updated score_examples targeting the exact misroute patterns from TB2 v6 (chess-best-move at 0.20, train-fasttext at 0.20, mailing list server at 0.20, Raman spectrum at 0.15, VM SSH setup at 0.20). These give the classifier concrete calibration anchors for the \"looks simple but is hard\" pattern.\n\n**Acceptance criteria:**\n- Replace the Kimi card in `model-cards.ts` with the three-pattern version from commit `75e4e67219` on the `model-router` branch\n- Adapt any model-ID references from K2.5 → K2.6 (capabilities may differ slightly)\n- Run offline eval to confirm no regression from the K2.5→K2.6 model change\n- Verify `defineCandidate` still resolves correctly (card is keyed on `ModelID.KIMI_K2_6`)\n\n**Risk:** Low. The card text is a prompt-o