a\n2. Build a card following the same structure as Opus/Kimi: capabilities, strengths (with specifics), weaknesses (with domain breakdown), 15-17 scored examples spanning 0.05–0.95\n3. Key questions to answer from eval data:\n   - Where does MiniMax succeed that we'd currently route to Kimi? (potential cost savings)\n   - Where does MiniMax fail that Kimi succeeds? (routing boundary)\n   - What is MiniMax's effective \"ceiling\" — how hard a task can it handle?\n4. Validate in offline eval that the updated card improves 3-way routing accuracy\n\n**Dependency:** This pairs well with ROUTER-2 (cost-weighted selector). A detailed MiniMax card + cost-weighted selector would let us correctly route MiniMax for the simplest tasks, Kimi for moderate tasks, and Opus for hard tasks — a three-tier system the threshold selector can't express.",
