ith both `reasoning_effort: High` and `reasoning_effort: Off`. Compare pass rates and latency. Document findings and set the candidate to the optimal value.\n\n### 2. MiniMax M2.7 Card (Build from Scratch)\n\nRun TB2 or legacy-bench eval with MiniMax M2.7 as sole model to collect ground-truth pass/fail data. Build a full card following the same structure:\n\nKey questions to answer:\n- Where does MiniMax succeed that we'd currently route to Kimi? (potential cost savings — these become MiniMax strengths)\n- Where does MiniMax fail that Kimi succeeds? (routing boundary — these become MiniMax weaknesses)\n- What is MiniMax's effective ceiling? How hard a task can it handle?\n- Does MiniMax have unique failure modes vs Kimi? (e.g., worse at multi-file edits? Worse at longer sessions?)\n\nCritical differentiator: MiniMax does NOT support images (score 0.0 on any image task). The vision-aware per-message upgrade (PR #14088/CL-480) handles runtime, but the card must give the classifier strong signal here.\n\n**Reasoning effort validation:** Same as Kimi — test High vs Off on MiniMax-appropriate tasks. MiniMax targets the simplest tasks where reasoning overhead may be pure latency waste.\n\n### 3. Opus 4.7 Card (Verify)\n\nLower priority. Verify existing card against 4.7 eval data:\n- Are there new capabilities in 4.7 not captured?\n- Have any 4.6 weaknesses been resolved in 4.7?\n- Adjust scored examples if pass rates have shifted\n\n### 4. Cross-Card Validation\n\nRun full 75-fixture offline eval with all three updated cards together. Measure:\n- Modal accuracy (target: ≥80% on 3-candidate pool)\n- Macro F1\n- Per-candidate precision/recall\n- Unstable fixture count\n- Score distributions: do the three candidates form clear tiers? (Opus high, Kimi mid, MiniMax low on hard tasks; reversed on simple tasks)\n\n## Key Files\n\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/model-cards.ts` — card content lives here\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/defineCandidate.ts` — validates cards at boot\n- `packages/droid-core/src/model-router/candidates.ts` — references cards via MODEL_CARDS\n- `evals/router/headroom-fixtures.jsonl` — 75 labeled eval fixtures\n- `apps/scripts/src/router-eval/run.ts` — offline eval harness\n- Prototype reference: `model-router` branch commit `75e4e67219`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All `TODO(factory-router)` markers in `model-cards.ts` removed\n- [ ] Kimi K2.6 card uses three-pattern weakness structure (not flat domain list)\n- [ ] MiniMax M2.7 card has ≥15 scored examples from real eval data\n- [ ] Opus 4.7 card verified (or updated if capabilities differ from 4.6)\n- [ ] Reasoning effort validated for both Kimi and MiniMax (findings documented in PR)\n- [ ] Offline eval (75 fixtures, 3 trials, 3 candidates) shows ≥80% modal accuracy\n- [ ] No regression on existing correct routes (git/data-processing/infra still route cheap)\n- [ ] Fixture set expanded if needed to cover MiniMax-appropriate tasks (simple single-file edits, short Q&A)\n\n## References\n\n- Prototype card commit: `model-router` branch `75e4e67219`\n- TB2 v2-fixed production run: `router-kimi-card-v2-tb2-fixed_2026-04-16__23-46-59`\n- Engineering notes: `docs/model-router-notes.md`\n- Related tickets: CL-65 (prototype), CL-67 (launch MVP), CL-473 (MiniMax M3 eval)\nEOF\n)\n\nlq \"$(jq -n --arg desc \"$DESCRIPTION\" '{\n  \"query\": \"mutation($input: IssueCreateInput!) { issueCreate(input: $input) { success issue { identifier title url } } }\",\n  \"variables\": {\n    \"input\": {\n      \"teamId\": \"a2ed886b-5f39-4c90-b643-2e93af919b03\",\n      \"title\": \"Refresh all Router model cards with data-driven capability profiles\",\n      \"description\": $desc,\n      \"priority\": 1,\n      \"projectId\": \"bd6f9f88-e35f-4ee0-8110-e305028f02ed\",\n      \"assigneeId\": \"1d4e45a6-e7f7-4204-8063-5390d595fd87\"\n    }\n  }\n}')\" '.data.issueCreate'",
